                    <div class="align-items-center">
                        <h2 style="text-align:center">
                            <u>Beginnings</u>
                        </h2>
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                Household chemicals are harmful to water. Phosphates in detergents can lead to freshwater algal blooms that release toxins and deplete oxygen in waterways.
                                And all detergents destroy the external mucus layers that protect the fish from bacteria and parasites; plus they can cause severe damage to the gills.

                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                In recent years, with population growth, the demand for water resources has also increased, but the amount of water storage has decreased in recent years.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                We have collected some data on these two factors click the button below to view the chart to learn more.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-info" style="margin-left:700px; margin-bottom:15px" onclick="window.location.href='/Home/StatisticsForWaterUsageAndChemicals'">Learn Morem</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>
</div>


