<div class="container" style="margin-top:20px">
    <article>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-10 col-md-12 mx-auto">
                    <div class="align-items-center">
                        <h2 style="text-align:center">
                            <u>Our Missions</u>
                        </h2>
                        <div class="row" style="margin-top:30px">
                            <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
                                <img src="~/pic/chemical-pollution.jpg" style="margin-top:30px; width:100%; height:auto;box-shadow: 0 4px 8px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), 0 6px 20px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.19);" />
                            </div>

                            <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
                                <h5>Waterways Healthy</h5>
                                <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
                                    Household chemical products, such as detergents, they mainly contain two types of ingredients, phosphate detergents and surfactant detergents.
                                    Detergents that contain phosphates are highly caustic, and surfactant detergents are very toxic.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Do you want to know which products in your home contain these ingredients? Click the button below to learn more.
                                </p>
                                <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-info" id="RM" onclick="window.location.href='/Home/homePage'"><u>Read More</u></button>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <hr />

                        <div class="row" style="margin-top:30px">
                            <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
                                <img src="~/pic/water-usage.jpg" style="margin-top:30px; width:100%; height:auto;box-shadow: 0 4px 8px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), 0 6px 20px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.19);" />
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
                                <h5>Rain Water From My Roof</h5>
                                <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
                                    <p>
                                        Do you know that your roof can collect about 100,000L of rainwater!
                                    </p>
                                    Even though a lot of data shows the per capita use of water is decreasing over years with personal saving actions and more efficient home appliances. 
                                    However, an increase in the number of people means increased water supply, water storage, and water resources.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Click the button below to learn more.
                                </p>
                                <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-info" id="RM" onclick="window.location.href='/Home/Instruction'"><u>Read More</u></button>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
